						<h1>Our neurosurgeons treat brain tumors, aneurysms, metastatic disease and other brain disorders through accurate diagnosis, precision medical procedures, and effective rehabilitation.</h1>
						<div class="column1">
						<p>The brain acts as the body's control center. When patients experience problems with their vision, speech, memory or balance, or are troubled with headaches, seizures, loss of consciousness or paralysis, a neurological condition may be the cause. Our neurosurgeons will diagnose the condition through comprehensive neurological exams that include advanced diagnostic imaging such as Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI), Computer Tomography (CT) and Arteriogram.</p>
						<p>Problems such as brain injuries, brain tumors, aneurysms or Arteriovenous Malformation (AVM) are serious and may require Craniotomy surgery. Tremors and Parkinson's disease can be treated with advanced technologies such as Gamma Knife Radiosurgery and Deep Brain Stimulation.					</p>
